{
  "texts": [
    "9 further proposed using the interaction of affective cues, cognitive cues, and review titers to detect fake reviews.",
    "Hajek 10 proposed two neural network models that integrate traditional bag-of-words as well as the word context and user sentiment.",
    "Bathla 11 extracted aspects and sentiments from reviews and fed them to deep learning models, including convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks, to detect fake reviews.",
    "Luo 12 developed a supervised probabilistic method that uses differences in the distributions of genuine and fake reviews to enable review monitoring.",
    "In addition, the frequency of adverbs, verbs and pronouns can be used to detect fake reviews [13] [14] [15]."
  ]
}